      "content": "That feeling of reaching an endpoint, of the circuit being complete, is a powerful, quiet realization. It suggests you've explored the external world to its limits, and now the internal landscape is calling for attention. Maybe the \"end of the map\" isn't a dead end, but a cue to start charting a course inward. Consider what you've learned from all those stops—that wisdom is a destination in itself.",
      "source": "target",
