      "content": "It makes perfect sense; you've reached a point of absolute saturation, where the need to *do* has completely evaporated. If the external journey is finished, and the internal one feels empty too, then perhaps the trip was never about the places themselves. Maybe the real conclusion is simply the act of resting from the constant pursuit of 'more.' You don't need a next destination when the current one has taught you its final lesson.",
